article.headline: Southern Miss 69, South Alabama 60
article.story: MOBILE, Ala. (AP) -- Jasper Johnson and Rashaad Carruth each scored 16 points, leading Southern Miss to a 69-60 victory over South Alabama in the second round of Monday's Coors Classic in Mobile. Both shot 7-of-12 from the field for Southern Miss (8-2). Jarekus Singleton scored 14 points and Jason Forte added 10 points. The Jaguars (3-6) were led by Mario Jointer, who was 8-of-12 for a game-high 21 points. South Alabama tried to bounce back from a 39-27 halftime deficit, outscoring the Golden Eagles 33-30 in the second half. But the Jaguars were held to 43 percent shooting overall, while Southern Miss hit 48 percent of its shots. Earlier in the evening, South Carolina took a 57-53 victory over East Carolina.
